    "83477156": {
      "title": "Climate, health, agricultural and economic impacts of tighter vehicle-emission standards",
      "abstract": "Vehicle-emission standards for non-carbon-dioxide pollutants have recognized benefits for air quality. An interdisciplinary analysis now shows that adopting tight on-road emission standards for these pollutants would also mitigate short-term climate change and provide large benefits for human health and food security in a number of developing countries."
